<br>
I believe this to be intentional and a good thing. The Epic is a part of the progression through the 50s, a very significant part of a characters career, particularly if they are not powerlevelled. I know it was basically a full year playing reasonably regularly for me to move through the 60s - I didn't rush it but I also didn't not care about levelling.<br>
<br>
As I have noted somewhere else, the Epic is head and shoulders above the pets up until level 61. Should a level 61 player have to do a 2 year old very difficult quest just to keep up? I say no.<br>
<br>
I have only very recently gotten my Epic. My initial reaction to it being superceded was sadness, and now that I have the spells and am only awaiting a level ding to 62 to try them, I am excited. <br>
<br>
I will continue to use my Rave Stick because it is in itself, pet aside, the finest weapon I own. But his time, for me, has come. I am storming the home of the Gods themselves and my plunder is their knowledge. <br>
<br>
A quest whose result is not even the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>ultimate Mastery</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> cannot hope to compete with this new power. Soon I will bid Epic Bober goodbye, and won;t look back. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=etadanikm>EtadanikM</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#333333>(11/3/02 4:00:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=815.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Try this on for size... :)</span><hr size=1> Embracing Darkness<br>
1:  Decrease Hitpoints by 68 (L63) to 70 (L65) per tick <br>
2:  Decrease Movement by 73% (L63) to 75% (L65) <br>
Mana cost: 200<br>
Casting time: 3.2<br>
Duration: 2.0 minutes<br>
NEC/63<br>
<br>
Mages aren't the only class whose epic has become obsolete.  Try this necro spell on for size.  Half the casting time, better snare, and lasts 20 seconds or so longer.  Sure, it doesn't TOTALLY outclass the epic in that it's not &quot;free&quot; damage, but what's 200 mana to a necro who regens 70+ mana/tick? The longer duration and shorter casting time easily makes up for the loss of 200 mana.  But, the necro epic saves the necro a spell slot, you say? Well what's he going to use that slot for? This isn't just a better snare - it's an awesome DoT to boot.  I really don't think that, with this spell, the necro epic would still be a more preferrable snare at all.<br>
<br>
Come on, epics aren't made to be the end all be all of equipment.  They were made for their time, to strengthen the casters of their time, but like any melee epic, their time will pass.  Be glad that epic2 is very possibly in the game atm, and that from all the rumors I've heard, it'll require epic1.  So you really haven't &quot;wasted&quot; 200+ hours doing epic1, because in order to get epic2, you'd have to spend that time ANYWAY.<br>
